1482.sql: WITH consumption_data AS (SELECT customerid, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013 FROM yearmonth GROUP BY customerid), percentage_increase AS (SELECT c.segment, ((cd.consumption_2013 - cd.consumption_2012) / cd.consumption_2012) * 100 AS percent_increase FROM consumption_data AS cd INNER JOIN customers AS c ON cd.customerid = c.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'EUR' AND cd.consumption_2012 > 0 AND cd.consumption_2013 > 0), segment_stats AS (SELECT segment, AVG(percent_increase) AS avg_percent_increase FROM percentage_increase GROUP BY segment) SELECT segment, avg_percent_increase FROM segment_stats WHERE segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') ORDER BY avg_percent_increase DESC

WITH consumption_data AS (SELECT customerid, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013 FROM yearmonth GROUP BY customerid), percentage_increase AS (SELECT c.segment, ((cd.consumption_2013 - cd.consumption_2012) / cd.consumption_2012) * 100 AS percent_increase FROM consumption_data AS cd INNER JOIN customers AS c ON cd.customerid = c.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'EUR' AND cd.consumption_2012 > 0 AND cd.consumption_2013 > 0), segment_stats AS (SELECT segment, AVG(percent_increase) AS avg_percent_increase FROM percentage_increase GROUP BY segment) SELECT segment, avg_percent_increase FROM segment_stats WHERE segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') ORDER BY avg_percent_increase DESC

WITH consumption2012 AS (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2012 FROM yearmonth WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', date) = '2012'), consumption2013 AS (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2013 FROM yearmonth WHERE STRFTIME('%Y', date) = '2013'), segmentconsumption AS (SELECT c.segment, COALESCE(c2.consumption2012, 0) AS consumption2012, COALESCE(c3.consumption2013, 0) AS consumption2013 FROM customers AS c LEFT JOIN consumption2012 AS c2 ON c.customerid = c2.customerid LEFT JOIN consumption2013 AS c3 ON c.customerid = c3.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'EUR'), percentageincrease AS (SELECT segment, CASE WHEN consumption2013 = 0 THEN 0 ELSE ((consumption2013 - consumption2012) / consumption2013) * 100 END AS percentageincrease FROM segmentconsumption) SELECT segment, AVG(percentageincrease) AS avgpercentageincrease FROM percentageincrease GROUP BY segment ORDER BY avgpercentageincrease DESC LIMIT 1

WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT c.segment, y1.consumption AS consumption_2012, y2.consumption AS consumption_2013 FROM yearmonth AS y1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y2 ON y1.customerid = y2.customerid INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y1.customerid = c.customerid WHERE y1.date LIKE '2012%' AND y2.date LIKE '2013%' AND c.currency = 'EUR'), percentagechange AS (SELECT segment, ((consumption_2013 - consumption_2012) / consumption_2013) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM consumptiondata) SELECT segment, AVG(percentage_increase) AS avg_percentage_increase FROM percentagechange GROUP BY segment ORDER BY avg_percentage_increase DESC

WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT c.segment, y1.consumption AS consumption_2012, y2.consumption AS consumption_2013 FROM yearmonth AS y1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y2 ON y1.customerid = y2.customerid INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y1.customerid = c.customerid WHERE y1.date LIKE '2012%' AND y2.date LIKE '2013%' AND c.currency = 'EUR'), percentagechange AS (SELECT segment, ((consumption_2013 - consumption_2012) / consumption_2012) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM consumptiondata) SELECT segment, AVG(percentage_increase) AS avg_percentage_increase FROM percentagechange GROUP BY segment ORDER BY avg_percentage_increase DESC

WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT c.segment, CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END AS consumption_2012, CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END AS consumption_2013 FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'EUR'), segmentconsumption AS (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption_2012) AS total_consumption_2012, SUM(consumption_2013) AS total_consumption_2013 FROM consumptiondata GROUP BY segment), percentageincrease AS (SELECT segment, ((total_consumption_2013 - total_consumption_2012) / total_consumption_2013) * 100 AS percent_increase FROM segmentconsumption) SELECT segment, percent_increase FROM percentageincrease WHERE percent_increase = (SELECT MAX(percent_increase) FROM percentageincrease) OR percent_increase = (SELECT MIN(percent_increase) FROM percentageincrease)

SELECT segment, MAX(percentageincrease) AS maxincrease, MIN(percentageincrease) AS minincrease FROM (SELECT t1.segment, ((t3.consumption2013 - t2.consumption2012) / t3.consumption2013) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM customers AS t1 JOIN (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2012 FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2012') AS t2 ON t1.customerid = t2.customerid JOIN (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2013 FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2013') AS t3 ON t1.customerid = t3.customerid WHERE t1.currency = 'EUR') AS subquery GROUP BY segment

SELECT segment, MAX(CASE WHEN consumption2012 <> 0 THEN ((consumption2013 - consumption2012) / consumption2012) * 100 END) AS maxincrease, MIN(CASE WHEN consumption2012 <> 0 THEN ((consumption2013 - consumption2012) / consumption2012) * 100 END) AS minincrease FROM (SELECT t1.segment, t2.consumption AS consumption2012, t3.consumption AS consumption2013 FROM customers AS t1 JOIN yearmonth AS t2 ON t1.customerid = t2.customerid AND SUBSTRING(t2.date, 1, 4) = '2012' JOIN yearmonth AS t3 ON t1.customerid = t3.customerid AND SUBSTRING(t3.date, 1, 4) = '2013' WHERE t1.currency = 'EUR') AS subquery GROUP BY segment

WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT c.segment, y.customerid, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) AS year, y.consumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS t ON c.customerid = t.customerid INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013')), percentageincreases AS (SELECT cd1.segment, ((cd2.consumption - cd1.consumption) / cd1.consumption) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM consumptiondata AS cd1 INNER JOIN consumptiondata AS cd2 ON cd1.customerid = cd2.customerid AND cd1.segment = cd2.segment WHERE cd1.year = '2012' AND cd2.year = '2013') SELECT segment, MAX(percentageincrease) AS maxincrease, MIN(percentageincrease) AS minincrease FROM percentageincreases GROUP BY segment

WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT c.segment, y.customerid, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) AS year, y.consumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN transactions_1k AS t ON c.customerid = t.customerid INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013')), percentageincreases AS (SELECT cd1.segment, (cd2.consumption - cd1.consumption) / cd2.consumption * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM consumptiondata AS cd1 INNER JOIN consumptiondata AS cd2 ON cd1.customerid = cd2.customerid AND cd1.segment = cd2.segment WHERE cd1.year = '2012' AND cd2.year = '2013') SELECT segment, MAX(percentageincrease) AS maxincrease, MIN(percentageincrease) AS minincrease FROM percentageincreases GROUP BY segment

WITH consumption2012 AS (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2012 FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2012'), consumption2013 AS (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2013 FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2013'), increasecalculation AS (SELECT c2012.customerid, (c2013.consumption2013 - c2012.consumption2012) AS increase FROM consumption2012 AS c2012 INNER JOIN consumption2013 AS c2013 ON c2012.customerid = c2013.customerid), percentageincreasecalculation AS (SELECT ic.customerid, (ic.increase / c2013.consumption2013) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM increasecalculation AS ic INNER JOIN consumption2013 AS c2013 ON ic.customerid = c2013.customerid), segmentpercentageincrease AS (SELECT c.segment, AVG(p.percentageincrease) AS avgpercentageincrease FROM percentageincreasecalculation AS p INNER JOIN customers AS c ON p.customerid = c.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY c.segment) SELECT segment, avgpercentageincrease FROM segmentpercentageincrease WHERE avgpercentageincrease = (SELECT MAX(avgpercentageincrease) FROM segmentpercentageincrease) OR avgpercentageincrease = (SELECT MIN(avgpercentageincrease) FROM segmentpercentageincrease)

WITH consumption2012 AS (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2012 FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2012'), consumption2013 AS (SELECT customerid, consumption AS consumption2013 FROM yearmonth WHERE SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2013'), increasecalculation AS (SELECT c2012.customerid, (c2013.consumption2013 - c2012.consumption2012) AS increase FROM consumption2012 AS c2012 INNER JOIN consumption2013 AS c2013 ON c2012.customerid = c2013.customerid), percentageincreasecalculation AS (SELECT ic.customerid, (ic.increase / c2013.consumption2013) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM increasecalculation AS ic INNER JOIN consumption2013 AS c2013 ON ic.customerid = c2013.customerid), segmentpercentageincrease AS (SELECT c.segment, AVG(p.percentageincrease) AS avgpercentageincrease FROM percentageincreasecalculation AS p INNER JOIN customers AS c ON p.customerid = c.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY c.segment) SELECT segment, avgpercentageincrease FROM segmentpercentageincrease WHERE avgpercentageincrease = (SELECT MAX(avgpercentageincrease) FROM segmentpercentageincrease) OR avgpercentageincrease = (SELECT MIN(avgpercentageincrease) FROM segmentpercentageincrease)

WITH yearly_consumption AS (SELECT c.segment, y.customerid, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) AS year, y.consumption FROM yearmonth AS y INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.customerid = c.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013')), percentage_increase AS (SELECT yc1.segment, (yc3.consumption - yc1.consumption) * 100.0 / yc3.consumption AS percentincrease FROM yearly_consumption AS yc1 INNER JOIN yearly_consumption AS yc3 ON yc1.customerid = yc3.customerid AND yc1.segment = yc3.segment WHERE yc1.year = '2012' AND yc3.year = '2013') SELECT segment, percentincrease FROM percentage_increase WHERE percentincrease = (SELECT MAX(percentincrease) FROM percentage_increase) OR percentincrease = (SELECT MIN(percentincrease) FROM percentage_increase)

WITH percentage_increases AS (SELECT c2012.segment, CASE WHEN c2013.total_consumption_2013 = 0 THEN NULL ELSE ((c2013.total_consumption_2013 - c2012.total_consumption_2012) / c2013.total_consumption_2013) * 100 END AS percentage_increase FROM (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) AS total_consumption_2012 FROM customers INNER JOIN yearmonth ON customers.customerid = yearmonth.customerid WHERE currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' GROUP BY segment) AS c2012 INNER JOIN (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) AS total_consumption_2013 FROM customers INNER JOIN yearmonth ON customers.customerid = yearmonth.customerid WHERE currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY segment) AS c2013 ON c2012.segment = c2013.segment) SELECT segment, percentage_increase FROM percentage_increases WHERE percentage_increase = (SELECT MAX(percentage_increase) FROM percentage_increases) OR percentage_increase = (SELECT MIN(percentage_increase) FROM percentage_increases)

WITH percentage_increases AS (SELECT c2012.segment, ((c2013.total_consumption_2013 - c2012.total_consumption_2012) / c2012.total_consumption_2012) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) AS total_consumption_2012 FROM customers INNER JOIN yearmonth ON customers.customerid = yearmonth.customerid WHERE currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' GROUP BY segment) AS c2012 INNER JOIN (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) AS total_consumption_2013 FROM customers INNER JOIN yearmonth ON customers.customerid = yearmonth.customerid WHERE currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY segment) AS c2013 ON c2012.segment = c2013.segment) SELECT segment, percentage_increase FROM percentage_increases WHERE percentage_increase = (SELECT MAX(percentage_increase) FROM percentage_increases) OR percentage_increase = (SELECT MIN(percentage_increase) FROM percentage_increases)

WITH percentageincreases AS (WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT c.segment, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) AS year, SUM(y.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM yearmonth AS y INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') AND c.currency = 'EUR' GROUP BY c.segment, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4)) SELECT c2012.segment, CASE WHEN c2012.totalconsumption = 0 THEN NULL ELSE ((c2013.totalconsumption - c2012.totalconsumption) / c2012.totalconsumption) * 100 END AS percentageincrease FROM consumptiondata AS c2012 INNER JOIN consumptiondata AS c2013 ON c2012.segment = c2013.segment WHERE c2012.year = '2012' AND c2013.year = '2013') SELECT segment, percentageincrease FROM percentageincreases WHERE percentageincrease = (SELECT MAX(percentageincrease) FROM percentageincreases) UNION ALL SELECT segment, percentageincrease FROM percentageincreases WHERE percentageincrease = (SELECT MIN(percentageincrease) FROM percentageincreases)

WITH percentageincreases AS (WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT segment, SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) AS year, SUM(yearmonth.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.customerid = customers.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') AND customers.currency = 'EUR' GROUP BY customers.segment, SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4)) SELECT c2012.segment, ((c2013.totalconsumption - c2012.totalconsumption) / c2012.totalconsumption) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM consumptiondata AS c2012 INNER JOIN consumptiondata AS c2013 ON c2012.segment = c2013.segment WHERE c2012.year = '2012' AND c2013.year = '2013') SELECT segment, percentageincrease FROM percentageincreases WHERE percentageincrease = (SELECT MAX(percentageincrease) FROM percentageincreases) UNION ALL SELECT segment, percentageincrease FROM percentageincreases WHERE percentageincrease = (SELECT MIN(percentageincrease) FROM percentageincreases)

WITH consumption_2012 AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) AS total_consumption_2012 FROM customers AS c JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND c.currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' GROUP BY c.segment), consumption_2013 AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) AS total_consumption_2013 FROM customers AS c JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND c.currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY c.segment), percentage_change AS (SELECT c2012.segment, (c2013.total_consumption_2013 - c2012.total_consumption_2012) AS increase_or_decrease, ((c2013.total_consumption_2013 - c2012.total_consumption_2012) / c2012.total_consumption_2012) * 100 AS percentage_of_increase FROM consumption_2012 AS c2012 JOIN consumption_2013 AS c2013 ON c2012.segment = c2013.segment) SELECT (SELECT segment FROM percentage_change ORDER BY percentage_of_increase DESC LIMIT 1) AS segment_biggest_increase, (SELECT segment FROM percentage_change ORDER BY percentage_of_increase ASC LIMIT 1) AS segment_lowest_increase

WITH consumption_2012 AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) AS total_consumption_2012 FROM customers AS c JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND c.currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' GROUP BY c.segment), consumption_2013 AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) AS total_consumption_2013 FROM customers AS c JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND c.currency = 'EUR' AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY c.segment), percentage_change AS (SELECT c2012.segment, (c2013.total_consumption_2013 - c2012.total_consumption_2012) AS increase_or_decrease, ((c2013.total_consumption_2013 - c2012.total_consumption_2012) / c2012.total_consumption_2012) * 100 AS percentage_of_increase FROM consumption_2012 AS c2012 JOIN consumption_2013 AS c2013 ON c2012.segment = c2013.segment) SELECT (SELECT segment FROM percentage_change ORDER BY percentage_of_increase DESC LIMIT 1) AS segment_biggest_increase, (SELECT segment FROM percentage_change ORDER BY percentage_of_increase ASC LIMIT 1) AS segment_lowest_increase

WITH consumption_data AS (SELECT c.segment, y.customerid, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) AS year, y.consumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND c.currency = 'EUR'), consumption_diff AS (SELECT cd1.segment, cd1.customerid, cd1.consumption - cd2.consumption AS consumptiondiff, cd2.consumption AS consumption2012 FROM consumption_data AS cd1 INNER JOIN consumption_data AS cd2 ON cd1.customerid = cd2.customerid AND cd1.segment = cd2.segment WHERE cd1.year = '2013' AND cd2.year = '2012') SELECT segment, MAX(percentageincrease) AS maxpercentageincrease, MIN(percentageincrease) AS minpercentageincrease FROM (SELECT segment, (consumptiondiff / consumption2012) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM consumption_diff) AS percentage_increase GROUP BY segment

SELECT c.segment, MAX(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y2013.date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND SUBSTRING(y2012.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN ((y2013.consumption - y2012.consumption) / y2013.consumption) * 100 ELSE NULL END) AS maxincrease, MIN(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y2013.date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND SUBSTRING(y2012.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN ((y2013.consumption - y2012.consumption) / y2013.consumption) * 100 ELSE NULL END) AS minincrease FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y2012 ON c.customerid = y2012.customerid AND SUBSTRING(y2012.date, 1, 4) = '2012' INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y2013 ON c.customerid = y2013.customerid AND SUBSTRING(y2013.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY c.segment

WITH filtered_customers AS (SELECT customerid, segment FROM customers WHERE currency = 'EUR' AND segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM')), consumption_data AS (SELECT fc.customerid, fc.segment, ym.date, ym.consumption FROM filtered_customers AS fc INNER JOIN yearmonth AS ym ON fc.customerid = ym.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(ym.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013')), calculated_increases AS (SELECT cd1.segment, ((cd2.consumption - cd1.consumption) / cd1.consumption) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM consumption_data AS cd1 INNER JOIN consumption_data AS cd2 ON cd1.customerid = cd2.customerid AND cd1.segment = cd2.segment WHERE SUBSTRING(cd1.date, 1, 4) = '2012' AND SUBSTRING(cd2.date, 1, 4) = '2013') SELECT segment, MAX(percentage_increase) AS max_percentage_increase, MIN(percentage_increase) AS min_percentage_increase FROM calculated_increases GROUP BY segment

SELECT segment, MAX(percentage_increase) AS max_percentage_increase, MIN(percentage_increase) AS min_percentage_increase FROM (SELECT c.segment, ((t2.consumption - t1.consumption) / t2.consumption) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM yearmonth AS t1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS t2 ON t1.customerid = t2.customerid INNER JOIN customers AS c ON t1.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(t1.date, 1, 4) = '2012' AND SUBSTRING(t2.date, 1, 4) = '2013') AS subquery GROUP BY segment

WITH filtered_data AS (SELECT y.customerid, y.date, y.consumption, c.segment FROM yearmonth AS y JOIN customers AS c ON y.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') AND c.currency = 'EUR'), consumption_diff AS (SELECT customerid, segment, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumptiondiff, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption2013 FROM filtered_data GROUP BY customerid, segment), percentage_increase AS (SELECT customerid, segment, (consumptiondiff / consumption2013) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM consumption_diff WHERE consumption2013 <> 0), avg_percentage_increase AS (SELECT segment, AVG(percentageincrease) AS avgpercentageincrease FROM percentage_increase GROUP BY segment) SELECT segment, avgpercentageincrease FROM avg_percentage_increase WHERE avgpercentageincrease = (SELECT MAX(avgpercentageincrease) FROM avg_percentage_increase) UNION ALL SELECT segment, avgpercentageincrease FROM avg_percentage_increase WHERE avgpercentageincrease = (SELECT MIN(avgpercentageincrease) FROM avg_percentage_increase)

WITH consumption_data AS (SELECT segment, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013, (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END)) AS increase_decrease, ((SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END)) / SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END)) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM customers INNER JOIN yearmonth ON customers.customerid = yearmonth.customerid WHERE customers.currency = 'EUR' AND customers.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY customers.segment) SELECT (SELECT segment FROM consumption_data ORDER BY percentage_increase DESC LIMIT 1) AS segment_biggest_increase, (SELECT segment FROM consumption_data ORDER BY percentage_increase ASC LIMIT 1) AS segment_lowest_increase

WITH consumption_data AS (SELECT segment, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013, (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END)) AS increase_decrease, ((SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END)) / SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END)) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM customers INNER JOIN yearmonth ON customers.customerid = yearmonth.customerid WHERE customers.currency = 'EUR' AND customers.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY customers.segment) SELECT (SELECT segment FROM consumption_data ORDER BY percentage_increase DESC LIMIT 1) AS segment_biggest_increase, (SELECT segment FROM consumption_data ORDER BY percentage_increase ASC LIMIT 1) AS segment_lowest_increase

WITH yearly_consumption AS (SELECT c.segment, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) AS year, SUM(y.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') GROUP BY c.segment, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4)), consumption_diff AS (SELECT c.segment, MAX(CASE WHEN c.year = '2013' THEN c.totalconsumption END) - MAX(CASE WHEN c.year = '2012' THEN c.totalconsumption END) AS consumptiondiff, MAX(CASE WHEN c.year = '2012' THEN c.totalconsumption END) AS consumption2012 FROM yearly_consumption AS c GROUP BY c.segment), percentage_increase AS (SELECT segment, consumptiondiff, consumption2012, (consumptiondiff / consumption2012) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM consumption_diff WHERE NOT consumption2012 IS NULL AND consumption2012 <> 0) SELECT segment, percentageincrease FROM percentage_increase ORDER BY percentageincrease DESC

WITH yearly_consumption AS (SELECT c.segment, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) AS year, SUM(y.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') AND SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') GROUP BY c.segment, SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4)), consumption_diff AS (SELECT c.segment, MAX(CASE WHEN c.year = '2013' THEN c.totalconsumption END) - MAX(CASE WHEN c.year = '2012' THEN c.totalconsumption END) AS consumptiondiff, MAX(CASE WHEN c.year = '2012' THEN c.totalconsumption END) AS consumption2012 FROM yearly_consumption AS c GROUP BY c.segment), percentage_increase AS (SELECT segment, consumptiondiff, consumption2012, (consumptiondiff / consumption2012) * 100 AS percentageincrease FROM consumption_diff WHERE NOT consumption2012 IS NULL AND consumption2012 <> 0) SELECT segment, percentageincrease FROM percentage_increase ORDER BY percentageincrease DESC

SELECT c.segment, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013, (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END)) AS increase_decrease, ((SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END)) / NULLIF(SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END), 0)) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY c.segment HAVING consumption_2012 > 0 ORDER BY percentage_increase DESC

SELECT c.segment, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013, (SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END)) AS increase_decrease, ((SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END)) / SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN y.consumption ELSE 0 END)) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.segment IN ('SME', 'LAM', 'KAM') GROUP BY c.segment HAVING consumption_2012 > 0 ORDER BY percentage_increase DESC

WITH consumptiondata AS (SELECT customers.segment, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2012' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2012, SUM(CASE WHEN SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) = '2013' THEN yearmonth.consumption ELSE 0 END) AS consumption_2013 FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.customerid = customers.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(yearmonth.date, 1, 4) IN ('2012', '2013') GROUP BY customers.segment), percentagechange AS (SELECT segment, ((consumption_2013 - consumption_2012) / consumption_2013) * 100 AS percentage_increase FROM consumptiondata WHERE consumption_2013 <> 0) SELECT segment, percentage_increase FROM percentagechange WHERE percentage_increase = (SELECT MAX(percentage_increase) FROM percentagechange) OR percentage_increase = (SELECT MIN(percentage_increase) FROM percentagechange)

SELECT customers.segment, MAX(((t2.consumption - t1.consumption) / t2.consumption) * 100) AS maxpercentageincrease, MIN(((t2.consumption - t1.consumption) / t2.consumption) * 100) AS minpercentageincrease FROM yearmonth AS t1 INNER JOIN yearmonth AS t2 ON t1.customerid = t2.customerid AND SUBSTRING(t2.date, 1, 4) = '2013' INNER JOIN customers ON t1.customerid = customers.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(t1.date, 1, 4) = '2012' GROUP BY customers.segment

1481.sql: WITH filtered_data AS (SELECT ym.customerid, ym.consumption, c.segment FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(ym.date, 1, 4) = '2013'), least_consumption_customers AS (SELECT segment, customerid, SUM(consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM filtered_data GROUP BY segment, customerid), min_consumption_customers AS (SELECT segment, customerid, totalconsumption, RANK() OVER (PARTITION BY segment ORDER BY totalconsumption ASC) AS rank FROM least_consumption_customers), annual_average_consumption AS (SELECT segment, customerid, totalconsumption / COUNT(customerid) OVER (PARTITION BY segment) AS annualaverage FROM min_consumption_customers WHERE rank = 1) SELECT (SELECT annualaverage FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT annualaverage FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_difference, (SELECT annualaverage FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT annualaverage FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_difference, (SELECT annualaverage FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT annualaverage FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_difference

WITH filtered_data AS (SELECT c.segment, y.consumption FROM yearmonth AS y INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND c.currency = 'CZK'), segment_min_consumption AS (SELECT segment, MIN(consumption) AS minconsumption FROM filtered_data GROUP BY segment), segment_min_count AS (SELECT f.segment, COUNT(f.consumption) AS mincount FROM filtered_data AS f INNER JOIN segment_min_consumption AS s ON f.segment = s.segment AND f.consumption = s.minconsumption GROUP BY f.segment), segment_total_consumption AS (SELECT f.segment, SUM(f.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM filtered_data AS f INNER JOIN segment_min_consumption AS s ON f.segment = s.segment AND f.consumption = s.minconsumption GROUP BY f.segment), segment_avg_consumption AS (SELECT s.segment, t.totalconsumption / s.mincount AS avgconsumption FROM segment_min_count AS s INNER JOIN segment_total_consumption AS t ON s.segment = t.segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_difference

WITH filtered_data AS (SELECT c.segment, y.consumption FROM yearmonth AS y INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND c.currency = 'CZK'), segment_min_consumption AS (SELECT segment, MIN(consumption) AS minconsumption FROM filtered_data GROUP BY segment), segment_min_count AS (SELECT f.segment, COUNT(f.consumption) AS mincount FROM filtered_data AS f INNER JOIN segment_min_consumption AS s ON f.segment = s.segment AND f.consumption = s.minconsumption GROUP BY f.segment), segment_total_consumption AS (SELECT f.segment, SUM(f.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM filtered_data AS f INNER JOIN segment_min_consumption AS s ON f.segment = s.segment AND f.consumption = s.minconsumption GROUP BY f.segment), segment_avg_consumption AS (SELECT s.segment, t.totalconsumption / s.mincount AS avgconsumption FROM segment_min_count AS s INNER JOIN segment_total_consumption AS t ON s.segment = t.segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM segment_avg_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_difference

WITH minconsumptionpersegment AS (SELECT segment, MIN(totalconsumption) AS minconsumption FROM (SELECT customers.customerid, customers.segment, SUM(yearmonth.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.customerid = customers.customerid WHERE yearmonth.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY customers.customerid, customers.segment) AS consumptionpercustomer GROUP BY segment), leastconsumingcustomers AS (SELECT consumptionpercustomer.customerid, consumptionpercustomer.segment, consumptionpercustomer.totalconsumption / 12 AS annualaverageconsumption FROM (SELECT customers.customerid, customers.segment, SUM(yearmonth.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.customerid = customers.customerid WHERE yearmonth.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY customers.customerid, customers.segment) AS consumptionpercustomer INNER JOIN minconsumptionpersegment ON consumptionpercustomer.segment = minconsumptionpersegment.segment AND consumptionpercustomer.totalconsumption = minconsumptionpersegment.minconsumption) SELECT MAX(CASE WHEN segment = 'SME' THEN annualaverageconsumption END) - MAX(CASE WHEN segment = 'LAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption END) AS sme_lam_difference, MAX(CASE WHEN segment = 'LAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption END) - MAX(CASE WHEN segment = 'KAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption END) AS lam_kam_difference, MAX(CASE WHEN segment = 'KAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption END) - MAX(CASE WHEN segment = 'SME' THEN annualaverageconsumption END) AS kam_sme_difference FROM leastconsumingcustomers

WITH minconsumptionpersegment AS (SELECT segment, MIN(totalconsumption) AS minconsumption FROM (SELECT customers.customerid, customers.segment, SUM(yearmonth.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.customerid = customers.customerid WHERE yearmonth.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY customers.customerid, customers.segment) AS consumptionpercustomer GROUP BY segment), leastconsumingcustomers AS (SELECT consumptionpercustomer.customerid, consumptionpercustomer.segment, consumptionpercustomer.totalconsumption / 12 AS annualaverageconsumption FROM (SELECT customers.customerid, customers.segment, SUM(yearmonth.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM yearmonth INNER JOIN customers ON yearmonth.customerid = customers.customerid WHERE yearmonth.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY customers.customerid, customers.segment) AS consumptionpercustomer INNER JOIN minconsumptionpersegment ON consumptionpercustomer.segment = minconsumptionpersegment.segment AND consumptionpercustomer.totalconsumption = minconsumptionpersegment.minconsumption) SELECT SUM(CASE WHEN segment = 'SME' THEN annualaverageconsumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN segment = 'LAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption ELSE 0 END) AS sme_lam_difference, SUM(CASE WHEN segment = 'LAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN segment = 'KAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption ELSE 0 END) AS lam_kam_difference, SUM(CASE WHEN segment = 'KAM' THEN annualaverageconsumption ELSE 0 END) - SUM(CASE WHEN segment = 'SME' THEN annualaverageconsumption ELSE 0 END) AS kam_sme_difference FROM leastconsumingcustomers

WITH minconsumption AS (SELECT c.segment, MIN(y.consumption) AS minconsumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY c.segment), annualaverage AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT c.customerid) AS avgconsumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid INNER JOIN minconsumption AS m ON c.segment = m.segment AND y.consumption = m.minconsumption WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY c.segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS diff_sme_lam, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS diff_lam_kam, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'SME') AS diff_kam_sme

WITH minconsumption AS (SELECT c.segment, c.customerid, MIN(y.consumption) AS minconsumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY c.segment, c.customerid), mincustomer AS (SELECT segment, customerid, minconsumption FROM (SELECT segment, customerid, minconsumption, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY segment ORDER BY minconsumption ASC) AS rn FROM minconsumption) AS t WHERE rn = 1), annualaverage AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT c.customerid) AS avgconsumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid INNER JOIN mincustomer AS m ON c.customerid = m.customerid AND c.segment = m.segment WHERE SUBSTRING(y.date, 1, 4) = '2013' GROUP BY c.segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS diff_sme_lam, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS diff_lam_kam, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'SME') AS diff_kam_sme

WITH rankedconsumption AS (SELECT ym.customerid, ym.consumption, c.segment, ROW_NUMBER() OVER (PARTITION BY c.segment ORDER BY ym.consumption ASC) AS rn FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(ym.date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND c.currency = 'CZK'), leastconsumption AS (SELECT customerid, consumption, segment FROM rankedconsumption WHERE rn = 1), avgconsumption AS (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) / COUNT(customerid) AS avgconsumption FROM leastconsumption GROUP BY segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_diff, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_diff, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_diff

WITH filtered_data AS (SELECT ym.customerid, ym.consumption, c.segment FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid WHERE ym.date BETWEEN 201301 AND 201312 AND c.currency = 'CZK'), total_consumption AS (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM filtered_data GROUP BY segment), least_consumption AS (SELECT segment, MIN(consumption) AS minconsumption FROM filtered_data GROUP BY segment), customer_count_least_consumption AS (SELECT fd.segment, COUNT(fd.customerid) AS customercount FROM filtered_data AS fd INNER JOIN least_consumption AS lc ON fd.segment = lc.segment AND fd.consumption = lc.minconsumption GROUP BY fd.segment), annual_average_consumption AS (SELECT tc.segment, tc.totalconsumption / cclc.customercount AS annualaverageconsumption FROM total_consumption AS tc INNER JOIN customer_count_least_consumption AS cclc ON tc.segment = cclc.segment) SELECT aac1.annualaverageconsumption - aac2.annualaverageconsumption AS diff_sme_lam, aac2.annualaverageconsumption - aac3.annualaverageconsumption AS diff_lam_kam, aac3.annualaverageconsumption - aac1.annualaverageconsumption AS diff_kam_sme FROM annual_average_consumption AS aac1 CROSS JOIN annual_average_consumption AS aac2 CROSS JOIN annual_average_consumption AS aac3 WHERE aac1.segment = 'SME' AND aac2.segment = 'LAM' AND aac3.segment = 'KAM'

WITH filtered_data AS (SELECT ym.customerid, ym.consumption, c.segment FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid WHERE ym.date BETWEEN 201301 AND 201312 AND c.currency = 'CZK'), least_consumption AS (SELECT segment, MIN(consumption) AS minconsumption FROM filtered_data GROUP BY segment), customer_count_least_consumption AS (SELECT fd.segment, COUNT(fd.customerid) AS customercount FROM filtered_data AS fd INNER JOIN least_consumption AS lc ON fd.segment = lc.segment AND fd.consumption = lc.minconsumption GROUP BY fd.segment), total_least_consumption AS (SELECT fd.segment, SUM(fd.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM filtered_data AS fd INNER JOIN least_consumption AS lc ON fd.segment = lc.segment AND fd.consumption = lc.minconsumption GROUP BY fd.segment), annual_average_consumption AS (SELECT tlc.segment, tlc.totalconsumption / cclc.customercount AS annualaverageconsumption FROM total_least_consumption AS tlc INNER JOIN customer_count_least_consumption AS cclc ON tlc.segment = cclc.segment) SELECT aac1.annualaverageconsumption - aac2.annualaverageconsumption AS diff_sme_lam, aac2.annualaverageconsumption - aac3.annualaverageconsumption AS diff_lam_kam, aac3.annualaverageconsumption - aac1.annualaverageconsumption AS diff_kam_sme FROM annual_average_consumption AS aac1 CROSS JOIN annual_average_consumption AS aac2 CROSS JOIN annual_average_consumption AS aac3 WHERE aac1.segment = 'SME' AND aac2.segment = 'LAM' AND aac3.segment = 'KAM'

WITH yearmonth2013 AS (SELECT ym.customerid, ym.date, ym.consumption, c.segment FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(ym.date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND c.currency = 'CZK'), minconsumptionpersegment AS (SELECT segment, MIN(consumption) AS minconsumption FROM yearmonth2013 GROUP BY segment), lowestconsumptioncustomers AS (SELECT ym.segment, SUM(ym.consumption) AS totalconsumption, COUNT(ym.customerid) AS numcustomers FROM yearmonth2013 AS ym INNER JOIN minconsumptionpersegment AS mcs ON ym.segment = mcs.segment AND ym.consumption = mcs.minconsumption GROUP BY ym.segment), avgconsumption AS (SELECT segment, totalconsumption / numcustomers AS avgconsumption FROM lowestconsumptioncustomers) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_diff, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_diff, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_diff

WITH yearmonth2013 AS (SELECT ym.customerid, ym.date, ym.consumption, c.segment FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid WHERE SUBSTRING(ym.date, 1, 4) = '2013' AND c.currency = 'CZK'), totalconsumptionpercustomer AS (SELECT customerid, segment, SUM(consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM yearmonth2013 GROUP BY customerid, segment), minconsumptionpersegment AS (SELECT segment, MIN(totalconsumption) AS minconsumption FROM totalconsumptionpercustomer GROUP BY segment), lowestconsumptioncustomers AS (SELECT tcc.segment, SUM(tcc.totalconsumption) AS totalconsumption, COUNT(tcc.customerid) AS numcustomers FROM totalconsumptionpercustomer AS tcc INNER JOIN minconsumptionpersegment AS mcs ON tcc.segment = mcs.segment AND tcc.totalconsumption = mcs.minconsumption GROUP BY tcc.segment), avgconsumption AS (SELECT segment, totalconsumption / numcustomers AS avgconsumption FROM lowestconsumptioncustomers) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_diff, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_diff, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM avgconsumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_diff

WITH annualaverage AS (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) / COUNT(DISTINCT customerid) AS avgconsumption FROM (SELECT customers.segment, yearmonth.consumption, yearmonth.customerid FROM customers INNER JOIN yearmonth ON customers.customerid = yearmonth.customerid WHERE customers.currency = 'CZK' AND yearmonth.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312') GROUP BY segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annualaverage WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_difference

WITH filtered_customers AS (SELECT c.customerid, c.segment, y.consumption FROM customers AS c INNER JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'CZK' AND y.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'), min_consumption_per_segment AS (SELECT segment, MIN(consumption) AS minconsumption FROM filtered_customers GROUP BY segment), customers_with_min_consumption AS (SELECT f.customerid, f.segment, f.consumption FROM filtered_customers AS f INNER JOIN min_consumption_per_segment AS m ON f.segment = m.segment AND f.consumption = m.minconsumption), annual_average_consumption AS (SELECT segment, SUM(consumption) / COUNT(customerid) AS avgconsumption FROM customers_with_min_consumption GROUP BY segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_difference

WITH minconsumptionpersegment AS (SELECT c.segment, MIN(ym.consumption) AS minconsumption FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'CZK' AND ym.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY c.segment), totalconsumptionforminconsumers AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(ym.consumption) AS totalconsumption, COUNT(DISTINCT ym.customerid) AS numcustomers FROM yearmonth AS ym INNER JOIN customers AS c ON ym.customerid = c.customerid INNER JOIN minconsumptionpersegment AS mcs ON c.segment = mcs.segment AND ym.consumption = mcs.minconsumption WHERE c.currency = 'CZK' AND ym.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY c.segment), avgannualconsumptionpersegment AS (SELECT tc.segment, tc.totalconsumption / tc.numcustomers AS avgannualconsumption FROM totalconsumptionforminconsumers AS tc) SELECT (SELECT avgannualconsumption FROM avgannualconsumptionpersegment WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgannualconsumption FROM avgannualconsumptionpersegment WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS diff_sme_lam, (SELECT avgannualconsumption FROM avgannualconsumptionpersegment WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgannualconsumption FROM avgannualconsumptionpersegment WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS diff_lam_kam, (SELECT avgannualconsumption FROM avgannualconsumptionpersegment WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgannualconsumption FROM avgannualconsumptionpersegment WHERE segment = 'SME') AS diff_kam_sme

WITH minconsumption AS (SELECT c.segment, MIN(y.consumption) AS minconsumption FROM customers AS c JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'CZK' AND y.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY c.segment), totalandcount AS (SELECT c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) AS totalconsumption, COUNT(c.customerid) AS numcustomers FROM customers AS c JOIN yearmonth AS y ON c.customerid = y.customerid JOIN minconsumption AS mc ON c.segment = mc.segment AND y.consumption = mc.minconsumption WHERE c.currency = 'CZK' AND y.date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312' GROUP BY c.segment), annualaverage AS (SELECT segment, totalconsumption / numcustomers AS avgconsumption FROM totalandcount) SELECT aa1.avgconsumption - aa2.avgconsumption AS sme_lam_difference, aa2.avgconsumption - aa3.avgconsumption AS lam_kam_difference, aa3.avgconsumption - aa1.avgconsumption AS kam_sme_difference FROM annualaverage AS aa1 JOIN annualaverage AS aa2 ON aa1.segment = 'SME' AND aa2.segment = 'LAM' JOIN annualaverage AS aa3 ON aa2.segment = 'LAM' AND aa3.segment = 'KAM'

WITH filtered_yearmonth AS (SELECT * FROM yearmonth WHERE date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'), total_consumption AS (SELECT y.customerid, c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM filtered_yearmonth AS y INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.customerid = c.customerid GROUP BY y.customerid, c.segment), min_consumption_per_segment AS (SELECT segment, MIN(totalconsumption) AS minconsumption FROM total_consumption GROUP BY segment), customers_with_min_consumption AS (SELECT tc.customerid, tc.segment, tc.totalconsumption FROM total_consumption AS tc INNER JOIN min_consumption_per_segment AS mcs ON tc.segment = mcs.segment AND tc.totalconsumption = mcs.minconsumption), annual_average_consumption AS (SELECT segment, SUM(totalconsumption) / COUNT(customerid) AS avgconsumption FROM customers_with_min_consumption GROUP BY segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_difference

WITH filtered_yearmonth AS (SELECT * FROM yearmonth WHERE date BETWEEN '201301' AND '201312'), total_consumption AS (SELECT y.customerid, c.segment, SUM(y.consumption) AS totalconsumption FROM filtered_yearmonth AS y INNER JOIN customers AS c ON y.customerid = c.customerid WHERE c.currency = 'CZK' GROUP BY y.customerid, c.segment), min_consumption_per_segment AS (SELECT segment, MIN(totalconsumption) AS minconsumption FROM total_consumption GROUP BY segment), customers_with_min_consumption AS (SELECT tc.customerid, tc.segment, tc.totalconsumption FROM total_consumption AS tc INNER JOIN min_consumption_per_segment AS mcs ON tc.segment = mcs.segment AND tc.totalconsumption = mcs.minconsumption), annual_average_consumption AS (SELECT segment, SUM(totalconsumption) / COUNT(customerid) AS avgconsumption FROM customers_with_min_consumption GROUP BY segment) SELECT (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') AS sme_lam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'LAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') AS lam_kam_difference, (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'KAM') - (SELECT avgconsumption FROM annual_average_consumption WHERE segment = 'SME') AS kam_sme_difference
